[{"location":"Risk_Functions/#Risk-Functions","page":"API","title":"Risk Functions","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Variance\nSD\nMAD\nSemi_SD\nFLPM\nSLPM\nWR\nVaR\nCVaR\nERM\nEVaR\nRRM\nRVaR\nMDD_abs","category":"page"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.Variance","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.Variance","text":"Variance(w::AbstractVector, Σ::AbstractMatrix)\n\nCompute the Variance of a portfolio with weights w and covariance Σ. Square of SD.\n\nmathrmVariance(bmw mathbfSigma) = bmw^intercal  mathbfSigma bmw\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.SD","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.SD","text":"SD(w::AbstractVector, Σ::AbstractMatrix)\n\nCompute the Standard Deviation of a portfolio with weights w and covariance Σ. Square root of Variance.\n\nmathrmSD(bmw mathbfSigma) = leftbmw^intercal  mathbfSigma  bmwright^12\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.MAD","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.MAD","text":"MAD(x::AbstractVector)\n\nCompute the Mean Absolute Deviation of a vector x of portfolio returns.\n\nmathrmMAD(bmx) = dfrac1T sumlimits_t=1^T leftlvert x_t - mathbbE(bmx) rightrvert\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.Semi_SD","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.Semi_SD","text":"Semi_SD(x::AbstractVector)\n\nCompute the mean Semi-Standard Deviation of a vector x of portfolio returns.\n\nmathrmSemiSD(bmx) = leftdfrac1T-1 sumlimits_t=1^Tminleft( bmx_t - mathbbE(bmx) 0right)^2right^12\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.FLPM","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.FLPM","text":"FLPM(x::AbstractVector, r::Real = 0.0)\n\nCompute the First Lower Partial Moment (omega ratio) of a vector x of portfolio returns with a minimum return target of r.\n\nmathrmFLPM(bmx r) = dfrac1T  sumlimits_t=1^Tmaxleft(r - bmx_t 0right)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.SLPM","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.SLPM","text":"SLPM(x::AbstractVector, r::Real = 0.0)\n\nCompute the Second Lower Partial Moment (Omega Ratio) of a vector x of portfolio returns with a minimum return target of r.`\n\nmathrmSLPM(bmx r) = leftdfrac1T-1 sumlimits_t=1^Tmaxleft(r - bmx_t 0right)^2right^12\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.WR","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.WR","text":"WR(x::AbstractVector)\n\nCompute the Worst Realisation or Worst Case Scenario of a returns vector x.\n\nbeginalign*\nmathrmWR(bmx) = -min(bmx)\n                      = max(-bmx)\nendalign*\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.VaR","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.VaR","text":"VaR(x::AbstractVector, α::Real = 0.05)\n\nCompute the Value at Risk of a returns vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1).\n\nmathrmVaR(bmx alpha) = -undersett in (0 T)inf left x_t in mathbbR  F_bmx(x_t)  alpha right\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.CVaR","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.CVaR","text":"CVaR(x::AbstractVector, α::Real = 0.05)\n\nCompute the Conditional Value at Risk of a returns vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1).\n\nbeginalign*\nmathrmCVaR(bmx alpha) = mathrmVaR(bmx alpha) - dfrac1alpha T sumlimits_t=1^T minleft( x_t + mathrmVaR(bmx alpha) 0right)\n                                    = mathrmVaR(bmx alpha) + dfrac1alpha T sumlimits_t=1^T maxleft( -x_t - mathrmVaR(bmx alpha) 0right)\nendalign*\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.ERM","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.ERM","text":"ERM(x::AbstractVector, z::Real = 1.0, α::Real = 0.05)\n\nCompute the Entropic Risk Measure of a vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1) for a given value of z.\n\nERM(x::AbstractVector, solvers::AbstractDict, α::Real = 0.05)\n\nCompute the Entropic Risk Measure at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1) by minimising with respect to z, using a dictionary of JuMP-supported solvers. This is because in general we don't know the value of z that minimises the function.\n\nmathrmERM(bmx z alpha) = z ln left( dfracM_bmxleft(z^-1right)alpha right)\n\nwhere M_bmxleft(z^-1right) is the moment generating function of bmx.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.EVaR","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.EVaR","text":"EVaR(x::AbstractVector, solvers::AbstractDict, α::Real = 0.05)\n\nCompute the Entropic Value at Risk of a returns vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1).\n\nmathrmEVaR(bmxalpha) = undersetz  0inf leftmathrmERM(bmx z alpha)right\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.RRM","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.RRM","text":"RRM(\n    x::AbstractVector,\n    solvers::AbstractDict,\n    α::Real = 0.05,\n    κ::Real = 0.3,\n)\n\nCompute the Relativistic Risk Measure of a vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1) and deformation parameter of κ ∈ (0, 1).\n\ntextrmRRM(bmx alpha kappa) = begincases\nundersetz t psi theta varepsilon omegainf  t + z ln_kappaleft(dfrac1alpha Tright) + sumlimits_i=1^T left(psi_i + theta_iright)\ntextrmst  -bmx - t + varepsilon + omega leq 0 \n z geq 0 \n left(zleft(dfrac1+kappa2kapparight) psi_ileft(dfrac1+kappakapparight) varepsilon_i right) in mathcalP_3^1(1+kappa) kappa(1+kappa) \n left(omega_ileft(dfrac11-kapparight) theta_ileft(dfrac1kapparight) -zleft(dfrac12kapparight) right) in mathcalP_3^1-kappa kappa\nendcases\n\nwhere ln_kappa(x) = dfracx^kappa - x^-kappa2 kappa and mathcalP_3^alpha 1-alpha is the 3D Power Cone.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.RVaR","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.RVaR","text":"RRM(\n    x::AbstractVector,\n    solvers::AbstractDict,\n    α::Real = 0.05,\n    κ::Real = 0.3,\n)\n\nCompute the Relativistic Risk Measure of a vector x at a significance level of α ∈ (0, 1) and deformation parameter of κ ∈ (0, 1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"Risk_Functions/#PortfolioOptimiser.MDD_abs","page":"API","title":"PortfolioOptimiser.MDD_abs","text":"MDD_abs(x::AbstractVector)\n\nCompute the Maximum Drawdown of a returns vector x using uncompounded cumulative returns.\n\ntextrmMDD(bmx) = undersetj in (0 T)maxleftundersetk in (0 j)maxleft( sumlimits_i=0^k x_i right) - sumlimits_i=0^j x_iright\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"idx/#PortfolioOptimiser-API-Index","page":"Index","title":"PortfolioOptimiser API Index","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"idx/","page":"Index","title":"Index","text":"","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"CurrentModule = PortfolioOptimiser","category":"page"},{"location":"#PortfolioOptimiser","page":"Home","title":"PortfolioOptimiser","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Home","title":"Home","text":"Documentation for PortfolioOptimiser.","category":"page"}]
